WEBVTT

00:00.383 --> 00:06.525
Use "so" before an adjective and "such" before a noun.

00:19.331 --> 00:20.673
It's so snowy.

00:21.045 --> 00:22.976
It's such a snowy day.

00:27.004 --> 00:29.741
This meeting is so boring.

00:30.679 --> 00:33.168
It's such a boring meeting.

00:37.068 --> 00:38.690
He's so tall!

00:39.447 --> 00:41.099
He's such a tall guy.

00:45.199 --> 00:47.193
So many people.

00:48.037 --> 00:50.216
Such a big crowd.

00:54.512 --> 00:56.887
It's so delicious.

00:57.570 --> 01:00.121
It's such a delicious sandwich.

01:04.121 --> 01:06.237
I'm so beautiful.

01:07.054 --> 01:09.357
I'm such a beautiful person.

01:13.337 --> 01:15.078
It's so nice out today.

01:15.871 --> 01:18.173
It's such a nice day.

01:22.608 --> 01:25.363
He is so lazy.

01:26.209 --> 01:28.697
He's such a lazy cat.

